“We are talking about an expansion of this successful project, but in the Czech Republic the negotiations do not seem to be particularly hopeful.
It will be more likely to enter the market of Mobilking in other countries in our region, as said in a telephone call for Mobil.cz Jana Studničková, the press spokesperson of the Penta financial group.
Indirectly, it confirmed that the current mobile telephone providers in the Czech Republic are not particularly disposed of in this regard.
On the contrary, they try to do everything to ensure that no potential competitor arises.
For a long time now, their interest in launching a virtual mobile phone provider has been showing the GTS Novera group, which wants to take a further step towards becoming a real competitor of Telefónica O2 in the field of corporate customers.
“We are very interested in offering our customers not only fixed network but also mobile telecommunications services.
