If it happens to you for the first time, in the best case, you will be scared, but in reality this has no meaning.
This is a positive sleep disorder called speaking in sleep.
It is widespread, especially among children and adolescents.
Certainly, more than one of you was told that you spoke at night.
This phenomenon can occur occasionally (one time in life, for example, as during high fever), or regularly (every day, once a week, once a month), the next day the child can remember nothing.
There is no single reason that causes this phenomenon.
Often, relationships with other appearances are sought in sleep, such as nightmares, panic fear at night, enuresis noctura (bed noses at night), talking in sleep, but there is no reason for it.
As we mentioned earlier, it can be on very high fever, stress situations or over-requirement.
In any case, this is a little researched phenomenon.
The frequency with which it occurs is very variable.
It may be that one speaks quietly in individual words, whispers or it can be quite an opposite (screaming, crying, long discussions ).
In cases where the expression is very intense, it is recommended that the child be monitored and consulted with a specialist to see if a problem exists, which causes anxiety and thus results.
We have said that it is a positive disorder, so it is not treated, whether it is associated with another sleep disorder that can be treated (for example, with sleep apnoea or with stress).
What you can do is perform a series of simple prevention measures:
Try not to raise the child before sleeping.
So, calm game for the child to choose and avoid stressful TV programs that are terrible and too wild.
Relaxation methods can be used to help the nervous children who are recommended to relax to get some inner rest.
This helps the child sleep quietly.
Once talking occurs in sleep, try to keep calm.
Remember that it is harmless for the child, and the next day it won't be possible to remember anything that happened.
Useful advice
Don't wake it up.
This is useless, because the child is unconscious, so you will get out of sleep.
Although the child speaks, it sleeps, so it rests.
Remembering that when it appears to be scary after a few appearances, it is recommended that you let yourself be consulted or find out what reason the child is afraid of.
When they understand what it says (which is not so usual), the child does not put pressure on them to make an appointment and get more information.
So you won't be able to achieve anything because when the child is sleeping, it's unconscious and can't think about it.
Moreover, you will hear what it says, but you will not know what it is dreaming and why it says that, therefore, they are careful with the interpretation of the information and the conclusions you draw from it.
Maybe it doesn't tell the child that you hear it at night and know its secrets.
Not even as a joke.
That's causing a lot of fear.
So, don't worry, it's nothing bad, it's a moment that takes just a few minutes.
