The possibility of extracting energy from the movements of the sea has been considered and examined for 70 years, and these studies have not accidentally intensified significantly since the first oil crisis.
When the price of oil fell by 1980, the idea of sea energy was gasled, but now the environmental organisations and the increased price of oil are pushing for new impetus in this sector.
The World Energy Council (WEC) in London estimates that 15% of the world's global energy needs could be covered by the energy generated by the ocean waves.
